<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 14:31:14 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>为什么我们都应该非常重视量子物理学</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/why-we-should-all-take-quantum-physics-extremely-personally</link><description>物理学被认为是一门冷酷的科学，但如果你以更多的主观性来看待它，它将改变你的生活，说&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/why-we-should-all-take-quantum-physics-extremely-personally.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 14:31:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/why-we-should-all-take-quantum-physics-extremely-personally</guid></item><item><title>维生素 D 类药物加化疗在胰腺癌试验中被证明是安全的</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/vitamin-d-like-drug-plus-chemotherapy-proves-safe-in-pancreatic-cancer-trial</link><description>FDA 批准的维生素 D 受体激动剂可能有助于安全地破坏胰腺癌肿瘤周围的致密基质，从而提供一种潜在的联合疗法。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/vitamin-d-like-drug-plus-chemotherapy-proves-safe-in-pancreatic-cancer-trial2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 14:16:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/vitamin-d-like-drug-plus-chemotherapy-proves-safe-in-pancreatic-cancer-trial</guid></item><item><title>通过衰变避免中微子质量张力</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/dodging-neutrino-mass-tension-with-decays</link><description>关于中微子质量估计的分歧可以通过假设中微子衰变成假设的无质量粒子来解决。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/dodging-neutrino-mass-tension-with-decays2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 14:01:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/dodging-neutrino-mass-tension-with-decays</guid></item><item><title>研究表明，肠道微生物释放调节肠道运动的激素信号</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/gut-microbes-unlock-hormone-signaling-that-regulates-gut-movement-study-suggests</link><description>全球有数百万人定期或长期受到肠道相关疾病的影响，例如肠易激综合征 (IBS)、胃食管反流病 (GERD) 和胃肠炎。因此，揭示有助于肠道健康的生理和生物过程可能非常有价值，因为它可能有助于设计更有效的干预措施来预防和治疗这些疾病。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/gut-microbes-unlock-hormone-signaling-that-regulates-gut-movement-study-suggests2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 13:46:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/gut-microbes-unlock-hormone-signaling-that-regulates-gut-movement-study-suggests</guid></item><item><title>受日本玩具启发的变形微型漫游车如何自主探索月球</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/how-a-shape-shifting-tiny-rover-inspired-by-japanese-toys-autonomously-explored-the-moon</link><description>月球任务有各种形状和大小，从装满科学设备的汽车大小的漫游车到高耸的火箭有效载荷，现在是一个大约手掌大小的小型变形机器。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/how-a-shape-shifting-tiny-rover-inspired-by-japanese-toys-autonomously-explored-the-moon3.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 13:31:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/how-a-shape-shifting-tiny-rover-inspired-by-japanese-toys-autonomously-explored-the-moon</guid></item><item><title>电子物质波获得超快扭矩，在飞秒内翻转旋手性</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/electron-matter-waves-gain-ultrafast-torque-that-flips-handedness-in-femtoseconds</link><description>从磁性到化学反应的许多自然过程都需要粒子在非常小尺度上的运动和旋转。在量子力学中，粒子表现出类粒子和类波行为，并且可以使用称为波函数的表示形式以数学方式描述它们的状态。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/electron-matter-waves-gain-ultrafast-torque-that-flips-handedness-in-femtoseconds.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 13:16:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/electron-matter-waves-gain-ultrafast-torque-that-flips-handedness-in-femtoseconds</guid></item><item><title>细菌如何使用乙酰辅酶作为细胞形成的组成部分</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/how-bacteria-use-acetyl-coenzyme-as-a-building-block-in-the-formation-of-cells</link><description>格赖夫斯瓦尔德大学的研究人员发现了一种新机制，枯草芽孢杆菌等细菌可以通过该机制调节中央代谢分子乙酰辅酶 A（乙酰辅酶 A）的产生。乙酰辅酶A，也称为活化乙酸，对于蛋白质、碳水化合物和脂质等营养物质的生产至关重要，因此在所有细胞的新陈代谢中发挥着关键作用。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/how-bacteria-use-acetyl-coenzyme-as-a-building-block-in-the-formation-of-cells.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 13:01:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/how-bacteria-use-acetyl-coenzyme-as-a-building-block-in-the-formation-of-cells</guid></item><item><title>Waymo 推出虚拟驾驶员模型来测试自动驾驶汽车碰撞避免</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/waymo-unveils-virtual-driver-model-to-test-autonomous-car-crash-avoidance</link><description>自动驾驶汽车已经在我们的一些街道上成为现实，并可能成为未来交通系统的主要组成部分。当然，与所有车辆一样，安全是主要问题。为了帮助评估和改进其自动驾驶技术，美国无人驾驶汽车公司 Waymo 创建了人类驾驶员在接近碰撞情况下行为的虚拟表示。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/waymo-unveils-virtual-driver-model-to-test-autonomous-car-crash-avoidance.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 12:46:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/waymo-unveils-virtual-driver-model-to-test-autonomous-car-crash-avoidance</guid></item><item><title>新型水基材料可以储存太阳能，在黑暗中进行反应，然后再充电</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/new-water-based-material-could-store-solar-energy-power-reactions-in-darkness-then-recharge</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 12:31:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/new-water-based-material-could-store-solar-energy-power-reactions-in-darkness-then-recharge</guid></item><item><title>研究人员发现与抑郁症相关的大脑“受困”模式</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/researchers-identify-brain-entrapment-patterns-associated-with-depression</link><description>西奈山伊坎医学院的研究人员发现了抑郁症患者大脑在活动状态之间转换的独特模式，为为什么抑郁症状会持续存在且难以克服提供了新的见解。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/researchers-identify-brain-entrapment-patterns-associated-with-depression.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 12:16:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/researchers-identify-brain-entrapment-patterns-associated-with-depression</guid></item></channel></rss>